<h3 id="multi-file-deployment">Multi-file Deployment</h3>

<p>Deploying multiple files on your Hub has never been this effortless. You can now provide a directory path to deploy all files within a directory to your Bump.sh hub.</p>

<p>For a more detailed walkthrough on how this works, check out the feature in action in our <a href="https://github.com/bump-sh/cli/releases/tag/v2.7.0">latest release notes</a>.</p>

<h3 id="live-preview">Live Preview</h3>

<p>Using the Live Preview feature  <code class="highlighter-rouge">bump preview --live my-definition-api.yml</code> now creates an immediate preview without waiting for the first change on the target file.</p>

<h3 id="other-improvements">Other improvements</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Keeping up with the latest version of the CLI is now easier thanks to a new warning in case of outdated version usage.</li>
  <li>Significant refactor of the deployment-related code to accommodate the new ‚ÄúMultiple files deploy‚Äù feature.</li>
  <li>CLI upgraded to TypeScript 4.5 and performed some dependency upgrades.</li>
</ul>
